In organized [[sport]]s, '''match fixing''' occurs as a match is played to a completely or partially pre-determined result, violating the rules of the game and often the law. The most common reason is to obtain a payoff from gamblers, but teams may also intentionally perform poorly to gain a future advantage, such as a better [[draft pick]]{{efn-ua|{{clear}}
